THE Board of Regents, Covenant University, Ota, has appointed Prof. Akan Williams as Acting Vice-Chancellor of the institution. Information Officer of the Institution, Attat Emmanuel, disclosed this in a statement on Wednesday in Ota. He said, “The appointment of Williams was approved on Tuesday, following the expiration of the tenure of the immediate past Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Aaron Atayero. “Williams was born on February 16, 1970, in Calabar, Cross River State. He is a native of Itoko, Ibesikpo-Asutan Local Government Area (LGA) of Akwa Ibom. “He is a Fellow of Chemical Society of Nigeria; a former Chairman, Ogun Chapter, Chemical Society of Nigeria; Member, Institute of Chartered Chemists of Nigeria; Member, Royal Society of Chemistry and a member American Chemical Society among others.” – NAN 